observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:
a.	Strictly comply with the provision of Section 287 of the Local Government Code of 1991 and the related DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 1, series of 2005 on the prompt and optimum utilization of the 20% DF in the implementation of priority development projects to attain socio-economic and environmental development of the city government;
b.	Utilize all balances of the 20% DF continuing appropriations for the implementation of development projects to attain the intended purpose for which the fund was appropriated;

c.	Require the City Engineer and all department heads with projects implemented out of the continuing appropriations to periodically submit to the City Budget Office the status of project implementation so that the latter can review and monitor balances pertaining to completed and unimplemented projects which will serve as the basis for the Local Finance Committee to recommend to the Sanggunian, thru the City Mayor, for reversion, those pertaining to completed projects and those no longer needed pursuant to Section  322 of R.A. 7160.
